{pp}
{bold}Show Events{nobold}
{pp}
Here are some events you can expect at the Ottawa Amiga Show.
Amiga Inc. will be there! Meet them in person and see all the latest
software and hardware.
{pp}
{fixed}
  * Play video games at the Amiga.info booth for a chance to win prizes!
    Highest score of the day will the winner!

  * We are thinking of having a Laser Quest game Saturday evening. Any
    comments or other ideas are greatly appreciated.

  * Room Reservations
    Rooms can be booked at the Travelodge Hotel. More information available
    shortly.
{left}
{pp}
{bold}Information for Vendors{nobold}
{pp}
The Ottawa Amiga Show will be trying a somewhat different format than most
Amiga shows. Each vendor at the show will have their own 300+ square foot
office to display all the latest Amiga hardware and software that they
have to offer.
{pp}
We have reserved an entire floor at the Travelodge Hotel where all vendors
will be conveniently located. We will supply signs for each vendor.
{pp}
    Here are some advantages to our format:{p}
{fixed}
        Low cost
        300+ square foot
        Desk and chairs
        Phone (with data port)
        Television (can be used for product demos)
        Private washroom
        Refreshments can be delivered to your room
        A personal atmosphere
{left}
{pp}
The costs for 1 office for 2 days (Saturday and Sunday) is only $300.00
including taxes [$195.00 USD]. There are some offices that have an
adjoinng door if you require more room. The cost for 2 offices will be
$575.00 [$370.00 USD].
{pp}
Additional rooms for seminars can be made available.
There will be media coverage of the event from Monitor Magazine, and local
media.
{pp}
We are also looking for companies to donate prizes for the show.
For more information and for payment information, please contact us at
amigashow@technomages.net.
{pp}
{bold}The Travelodge Hotel{nobold}
{center}
{image travelodge.iff}
{left}
{pp}
The Travelodge Hotel Ottawa West is located just a few minutes from
downtown and Parliament Hill via Highway 417 (Queensway). A full service
hotel, with beautifully landscaped grounds complete with oriental gardens,
ornamental pond and waterfall, is the perfect place to stay when visiting
Ottawa. A variety of restaurants, shopping and entertainment are all
within walking distance of our hotel.
{pp}
The hotel features 261 tastefully decorated guestrooms, remote control
cable television, complimentary coffee. Enjoy a delicious meal in the
on-site Village Restaurant and Lounge, which is open for breakfast, lunch,
and dinner daily from 7:00AM to 10:00PM.
{pp}
During your stay with us, experience the wonderful sites in Ottawa such as
Parliament Hill, Byward Market, and the National Gallery of Canada.
More information and directions to the Hotel will be available shortly.
{pp}
For additional information and questions about the Ottawa Amiga Show,
please email amigashow@technomages.net
{pp}
If you would like to be kept up to date on show announcements, send an
email to oas-subscribe@technomages.net and you will be subscribed to the
show's mailing list.
{pp}
